OwnedAttributes and ownedOperation correspond to remote variables and operations or better the signatures of such.

There is a little discrepancy with UML. In UML I could model a property, for instance an agent, to have none aggregation semantics. I can do that in SDL, but I could map it to an SdlVariable of PID type (this is suggested by Z.109), but the meta-model does not state something like that. On the hand there is no sence in giving a SdlVariable none aggregation semantics, because it can only contain values with value semantics. The multiplicity for variables is set to 1..1, but it could be meaningful to allow other multiplicities to model collection (types).
